# Handling Telephone Calls

## Answering the Phone

When answering the phone, I will greet the caller with a professional and friendly tone, stating the name of the practice or facility and my position as a medical secretary.

Example: "Thank you for calling [Practice/Facility Name], this is [Your Name], Medical Secretary. How can I assist you today?"

## Directing Calls to Appropriate Staff

Once I have answered the phone, I will assess the purpose of the caller's call and direct them to the appropriate staff member or department. This may include:

* Scheduling appointments with providers or other staff members
* Providing information or answering questions about patient care or medical procedures
* Transferring calls to other departments or facilities
* Taking messages and ensuring they are delivered to the correct staff member

I will always be mindful of the caller's needs and concerns, and strive to provide accurate and helpful information in a timely and professional manner.
</OUTPUT_TEXT>
